The man accused of raping a 6-year-old in Tshwane has been remanded in custody. The 20-year-old suspect appeared in Pretoria Magistrates Court on Tuesday facing charges of rape, drug possession and assault GBH. He will be back in court on 1 November pending investigations and the forensic report. The nation went into shock when it was emerged that the suspect had raped a 6-year-old child in a Dros outlet in Tshwane recently. A video circulated online showed the alleged rapist being confronted by people. The incident has been widely condemned by various sectors of society.